"Yatra" is a film about how Rajasekhara Reddy realized these problems during his journey. The solutions to it are well known, not shown, not even shown. translated: The provision of reservation in dent was made with the aim of ensuring that those who remained historically exploited and backward could also be represented in government services and educational institutions. But ironically, the general class, which has more representation than its population, is also being given reservation from above. Recently, the government made a provision of 10 percent reservation in jobs and educational institutions for the poor sections of the general category. For this, by amending the constitution, the 'economic base' was also made a reason for backwardness, whereas the original constitution only provided reservation on social and educational backwardness. The ruling party is loudly beating the opposition, while the opposition, which also includes the parties representing the so-called backward castes, is taking credit for their contribution by supporting this new reservation system for the vote of the so-called upper castes. It is argued that due to this new system, there will be no harm to the section already reserved. But upon deep analysis, it becomes clear that this new reservation system is directly hurt by the principle of reservation. Actually, the principle of reservation is related to representation. But the government made it a poverty alleviation program by providing reservation on economic grounds. The provision of reservation was made with the goal that those who remained historically exploited and backward also be ensured in government services and educational institutions. But ironically, the general class, which has more representation than its population, is also being given reservation from above. Recently published figures in The Indian Express also appear to confirm the over representation of the general categories. Making reservation a program of poverty alleviation is a direct attack on the reservation system and tarnishing its purpose. The purpose of reservation will be a direct loss to the Other Backward Classes (OBCs) and Dalits due to tarnishing. From a mathematical point of view, now the number of unreserved seats will decrease compared to earlier. For example, out of 100, 40 seats will remain unreserved, which used to be 50 earlier. As a result, competition for the backward classes will increase and the chances will be less to be selected from the unreserved seats. In contrast to all this, the sad thing is that the representatives of the backward classes are getting stuck in the arguments of the upper castes and yes instead of coming out in protest. The truth of our society is that the so-called upper castes have always been anti-reservation. Their effort has been that either the reservation be over or they get it too because getting reservation means that no one got reservation! Rahul Raj, Nawada, Bihar Political Chhattisgarh: Political parties have started playing the check and check by laying the chessboard for the Lok Sabha elections. The most important aspect of this game is that as usual the pawn will remain public. How to use this piece, these political parties are engaged in making diplomacy according to their own. Now political parties are more concerned with religious equation than caste. Participation of many parties in spreading hate is in front of everyone! The Muslim-cried culture of the home Muslim or the cried Muslim or the home-grown Muslim has now become rare. The irony is that the leaders of political parties are desperate to show the disgusting spectacle of communalism by wearing secularism cloak. As the elections draw closer, the chest locks of these leaders will be opened. But now the big question is, will the public not come under the guise of these political parties and play their part in strengthening the foundation of the country's secular and nationalism?

translated: Comprehensive Package for Idukki District worth Rs 5,000 Crore. The project aims to increase the production and value of tea, jackfruit, vegetables, spices, pepper and cardamom. Finance Minister TM Thomas Isaac told the Assembly that the package would be implemented within three years. As part of this, projects worth Rs 1,500 crore will be implemented in the financial year 2019-20. The Finance Minister explained that the Comprehensive Package is based on the specific proposal of Minister MM Mani. It aims to brand Tea, expand Spice Park and create a centralized marketing system for value-added products such as jackfruit. Idukki will now acquire a comprehensive dairy farming system and a Brahmagiri-based meat processing unit. The package will be made up of a combination of state-specific, centralized, local government, rebuild Kerala initiative and KIFB. More than Rs 550 crore from the state plan, 100 crores from the Centrally Sponsored Plans, 350 crores from local bodies, 250 crores from KFB and 250 crores from Rebuild Kerala. The district plan will be included in this. The Finance Minister said the package would be based on environmental considerations and integrated with people's lives and agriculture. Soil health card will be issued to all farmers after soil testing. The required manure, live manure, lime and dolomite will be made available to all farmers in the district before the monsoon season. Bio-fertilizer units will be started in Panchayats with the participation of Kudumbasree and Haritha Krsna Sena. Livestock production will be started at the existing crop health centers at block level. . Watershed based comprehensive land use planning will be implemented with the participation of the people. The focus will be on farm tourism. The second phase of the Botanical Garden at Munnar, the Tourism Department owned by the Idukki Dam and the Hydel Tourism are the major activities.

message_text: The notification is a big relief for the drivers as the previous law demanded them to present the physical documents (e.g. DL, RC, Pollution Check, and Insurance) as proof of eligibility to drive on Indian roads. This was a major concern not only for the drivers but even for the entire ecosystem including law and enforcement machinery, and the insurance industry. There were numerous problems that were being faced by the drivers in India due to the existing law including risk of misplacing DL/ losing it to theft, disfigured/torn documents, long discussions with the traffic police to prove the veracity of the documents, and delay in getting the physical documents from the concerned authorities.  Yet another common problem that the drivers in India face is that the hard copy delivery of insurance certificate is typically delayed on an average by 15-20 days. Moreover, as per a recent survey, on an average a driver gets delayed by 15 min to 4 hours in reaching the destination when asked for physical documents as proof of eligibility to drive on Indian roads. Fortunately, with the implementation of the new law, most of these concerns will be addressed.

There were numerous problems that were being faced by the drivers in India due to the existing law including risk of misplacing DL/ losing it to theft, disfigured/torn documents, long discussions with the traffic police to prove the veracity of the documents, and delay in getting the physical documents from the concerned authorities.  Yet another common problem that the drivers in India face is that the hard copy delivery of insurance certificate is typically delayed on an average by 15-20 days. Moreover, as per a recent survey, on an average a driver gets delayed by 15 min to 4 hours in reaching the destination when asked for physical documents as proof of eligibility to drive on Indian roads. Fortunately, with the implementation of the new law, most of these concerns will be addressed.

translated: * National President of Mission Security Council - with the pen of Gangaram ЁЯЦЛ  Ambedkar * ------ ЁЯШ┤ ЁЯШ┤ ЁЯШ┤ ЁЯШ┤  ЁЯШ┤   ЁЯШ┤   ЁЯШ┤   ЁЯШ┤  ЁЯЦЛ ЁЯШ┤ЁЯШ┤ЁЯШ┤ЁЯШ┤ЁЯШ┤ЁЯШ┤ЁЯШ┤ЁЯШ┤ _ May we not get stuck _----- _ Let us not go astray_рее ************************* Ambedkari movement sobering Bahujan caravan and devoid of direction - Let us contemplate, think and do some concrete work. During the era of Manyavar Shri Kanshi Ram Saheb, a slogan in the countryтАЩs Fijas was very fastтАж. _Now it's Bahujan's turn_ At that time, the wind of the ideology of the great men of Bahujan society from South India had taken the form of a storm, coming to India. In the short span of thirteen years, the Ambedkari ideology had become a major force of the country on the national horizon. From 1997 to 2007 ten years was at its peak. . But in the present era, Bahujan movement is going through rocky and inaccessible paths. The Ambedkari movement has become like a temperature measuring thermometer, whose basic element is mercury dispersed into the ground and missionaries want to work by melting silver instead of mercury and putting them in thermometers. The new inexperienced leadership in the Bahujan society is silver to mercury. Want to be understood with tweezers and fingers. The new leadership that emerged in Bahujan society, including ours, became like the magicians of the exhibition of magic. The mercury emanating from the thermometer, that is, the Bahujan society, which has spread like mercury after plunging into the ground, want to show them their tricks and pick them up with tweezers and finger and put them in the Ambedkari thermometer. Some big players are visible, they only want to send the scattered mercury to the destination. Some people are getting tired of showing juggles and making bamboos in the tent of enemies. Some people are reading Shayari without season like Mushayre's Besure Poet. Some people have become shopkeepers of the conduct of Meena Bazar, which took place in the era of Mughal emperors. Here in almost two years, Ramlila Maidan and Jantar Mantar Maidan have also become worried that who are these Jai Bhim Bale who give mea meena market in our chest every week and media hair is printed in the empty bottle of Bisleri liver I throw it away. Aspiring to connect and create society, less political aspirations have filled the weeds in the newly prepared crop of Bahujan society. Where can I get honest leadership like Baba Saheb Dr. Ambedkar and Bahujan Nayak Manyawar Mr. Kanshi Ram Sahab from where will the Bahujan society get it? This responsibility belongs not to any leader but to the Bahujan society itself. Otherwise, like South India, the way Ambedkari ideology has decorated its shops in Maharashtra, scattered in Maharashtra, the situation seems to be in Uttarabharat. Bahujan society stands at the crossroads of disorientation rather than awareness. Those who have the thinking, time, resources and people are victims of ego, ago, ego. Some people who have taken the benefit of reservation are helpful to the opponents in bringing power to themselves and Bibi. Hence the weak oppression of Bahujan society is helpless due to excess injustice, atrocities. How to get the mercury falling from Ambedkari thermometer again there Bring it smooth For this, there is no finger tweak, but the paper (paper) of Baba Saheb Dr. Ambedkar's thoughts and Bahujan Nayak Manyawar Shri Kanshi Ram Sahab's Bahujan Samaj should be made, ie economic, political and social change can happen only by the gathering of the victims of majority casteism. translated: Chief Minister Pinarayi Vijayan unveiled the logo of Kokonics, Kerala's own laptop server project. Industry Minister E.P. Jayarajan handed over the laptop to Kokonics. Kokonics' first line of laptops will be presented at the Electronic Manufacturing Summit in Delhi on February 11. Keltron, a public company, has partnered with UST Global, a global leader in electronics manufacturing, to launch its own line of quality laptops and servers in Kerala. Introduction of Kokonix, a public-private enterprise, is being developed with the guidance and technical support of Intel, a leading electronic equipment manufacturer. Kokonics is the first public-private enterprise in India to offer laptop server manufacturing. Kokonix has a tool manufacturer system that partners with Keltron and KSIDC, as well as UST Global and Acceleron (Intel India Maker Lab Accelerated Start-Up). The company is operating at a location that has been upgraded and made available in Keltron's Thiruvananthapuram earthenware facility. Kokonix focuses on the production of various electronic devices and equipment components suitable for government offices, educational institutions and business institutions. Kokonics has been operating with a production capacity of two and a half million laptops per year. Chief Minister Pinarayi Vijayan said that Kokonics is aiming at developing an active electronic hardware ecosystem in Kerala. Industry Minister EP Dhoni said Kokonix offers an opportunity to combine the capabilities of innovative start-up companies and small and medium-sized IT enterprises in the government and private sectors. It was also right in some circumstances to make a living 50-50 years ago. Teach, teach and earn respect, wages, jobs, business for this. Today the Shudra society is cheating itself and feeling cheated. The situation is as it is today. I couldn't sleep that night, why? BAMCEF missionary, what is the helplessness? Wherever I went, I kept questioning, arguing, even with Brahmins and with Chhatriyas, Vaishyas, backward castes, Dalits, even Muslims, Christians and intellectuals. Ahinsaivad eats the flesh of dead animals or the Hinsawadi Brahmin by cutting live cows. * Third * - Small - used to clean small chores and dirt. * Conclusion * - Is deception and crime working, or pretend and hypocrisy? translated: Parking of vehicles is the biggest problem for the people in the city. Due to which people have to park their vehicles on the road or track. In such a situation, an exercise has been started by the Department of Minorities to make multi-level parking in the city. So that people do not have to bother in erecting vehicles. Multi-label parking is proposed to be constructed in the city's vegetable market. For many years, there has been an ongoing exercise on the construction work on the land given for parking. A map was also prepared a year ago by the municipality. The place where the multi-label parking is to be constructed in the vegetable market. In that place vegetable used to be market in old time. After the market is built in Mahuli, people still keep their shops in that place but retail. It has been included in the Central Government's Prime Minister's Jan Vikas Program to create multi-label parking at that place. In view of the budget problem, the exercise of its construction has been handed over to the Minority Department. So that a parking lot is created. Shopping goods and shops will also be found in this multi level parking. This can provide relief to the shoppers coming from outside. People will get rid of the biggest problem in the city after parking. Suresh Chandra Singh, EO of the municipality says that the construction of his first multi-level parking would have been drafted. They do not know much about it yet. People will get rid of the biggest problem in the city after parking. Due to the delay, the MP wrote a letter to the Director, seeing the delay in the construction of multi-level parking in the city, MP Harivansh Singh has written a letter to the Minority Department. In which it is said that the construction of parking lot in the municipality area is to start. For which your department should prepare and provide its approval under the Pradhan Mantri Jan Vikas Program Scheme. So that work can be started in public interest. Apart from this, it is also proposed to construct a 1000-seat state-of-the-art hall in place of the old building in Hadihal. Construction of sports complex in the grounds of the Government Inter College is also included. The swimming pool also hangs in the balance. Under the Prime Minister's Public Development Program, a swimming pool is to be constructed for the convenience of the people in the stadium. For a long time, the department has been adopting an indifferent attitude towards the proposed swimming pool. Construction of Community Hall on vacant land of Circuit House and construction of 300 seated auditorium in Vikas Bhawan with parking is proposed. Construction of the gymnasium at the recreation center in the company Garden is also included in the plan. Which still hangs in the balance. For this, the MP has again sent correspondence.

translated: Gone are the days when the тАЬYatraтАЭ review was seeking another personтАЩs death for the next Rs 75 pension. The days when the farmer was unable to bear the burden of the increased electricity tariffs without a proper price for the harvested crop, and the reduction of more than ten thousand. Gone are the days when there were two lanes (one to die for, the other to sell to a family or a cook) to the hole in the heart of the baby. The days of sending a child to the home of any child who can not afford the cost of studying for a child. Any heart attack at midnight or pregnant delivery is torn apart, not knowing how to get to a hospital somewhere far away. "Yatra" is a film about how Rajasekhara Reddy realized these problems during his journey. The solutions to it are well known, not shown, not even shown. Initially, two short scenes focused on public appearances, despite the cynicism of the then ruling party and not the big criticism of the film. Vissar was shown to be more troubled by opponents within his own party than from the then ruling party. The movie is an asset. Also, the role of Vijayamma is well received. Both songs move. The RR seemed a little overboard at first, then nice. Photography is the highlight of the film. But when the movie was on foot, the details were lost, like how many kilometers were walked and over which districts. When you go to a movie called Yatra you should know all about the trip, but the details are not fully known, at least not as a slide at the end. The real scenes mix up when Vissar dies at the end, and feels complete. On the footsteps of a difficult subject of cinema, the heart is moving and director Mahi has succeeded. Congrats to the expedition team! Put aside politics and castes, come out and say your views. #YATRA

translated: * Discussion on Mainpuri Lok Sabha * Mainpuri Lok Sabha seat, considered a stronghold of Samajwadi Party, is a very important seat according to the 2019 elections. Samajwadi Party general secretary Mulayam Singh Yadav won the elections from here in the 2014 Lok Sabha elections, but he left this seat. After which his grandson Tej Pratap Singh Yadav reached the Lok Sabha by a big margin in the by-election. However, Mulayam Singh Yadav has been an MP from here many times before. The Mainpuri Lok Sabha seat has been in the discussion since the first elections held in the country. From 1952 to 1971, the Congress had won from here a total of 5 elections in the country. Although the Congress was defeated by the Janata Party in the 1977 anti-incumbency wave, the Congress withdrew the seat in the by-elections held in 1978 the following year. After that, in 1980, the Congress lost the seat and came back again in 1984 wave. In 1984, the Congress won the last time here, since then this seat has been in the possession of regional parties. In 1989 and 1991, the Janata Party consistently won here. But after forming the party in 1992, Mulayam Singh Yadav fought the 1996 election from here and also won by a big margin. After this, the seat remained with the Samajwadi Party in 1998, 1999. In 2004, Mulayam once again returned to this seat, but later left the seat. In 2004, Dharmendra Yadav won the by-election from here. However, Mulayam returned here in the 2009 elections and kept the seat with him. In the 2014 elections too, Mulayam won from here and gave this seat to his grandson Tej Pratap Singh Yadav. It is important that Jaswantnagar comes in Mainpuri area, which is Shivpal Yadav's assembly constituency. Shivpal Yadav is contesting from the Samajwadi Party this time to form his new party, in which case he can have a big impact on this seat too. Significantly, Shivpal Yadav had a strong hold on the organization even when he was in Samajwadi Party. According to 2014 figures, there are more than 16 lakh voters in Mainpuri Lok Sabha. Looking at the caste equation, this seat is dominated by Yadav voters, about 35 percent voters here are from the Yadav community. While around 2.5 lakh voters are Shakya. This has been the reason that a Chhatra Raj of the Samajwadi Party runs here. There are a total of 5 assemblies in this Lok Sabha constituency. Among them are Mainpuri, Bhogaon, Kishani, Karhal and Jaswantnagar. Please tell that Jaswantnagar is the assembly constituency of Shivpal Yadav. Of these, only Bhogaon went to the Bharatiya Janata Party's account in the 2017 assembly elections, while the remaining 4 seats went to the SP's account. The Modi wave in the 2014 elections had no impact on this seat and Mulayam Singh Yadav, the chief of the Tatkalani Samajwadi Party, won with a big margin. Tej Pratap Singh Yadav also won the election with a huge margin in the by-election held here after he left the seat. Tej Pratap Singh Yadav got around 65 per cent votes here, while the BJP candidate standing in front of him got only 33 per cent votes. In the 2014 by-election, there was around 62 percent turnout. Tej Pratap Singh Yadav is the third generation of Mulayam Singh Yadav's family. He won the 2014 election for the first time in politics, although he got a big advantage of contesting from Mulayam Singh Yadav's seat. Tej Pratap Yadav is also a part of several committees of Parliament. He has spent about 90 percent of his parliamentary quota. He has participated in 16 debates in the 16th Lok Sabha and has asked 226 questions.

translated: * Discussion on Mainpuri Lok Sabha * Mainpuri Lok Sabha seat, considered a stronghold of Samajwadi Party, is a very important seat according to the 2019 elections. Samajwadi Party general secretary Mulayam Singh Yadav won the elections from here in the 2014 Lok Sabha elections, but he left this seat. After which his grandson Tej Pratap Singh Yadav reached the Lok Sabha by a big margin in the by-election. However, Mulayam Singh Yadav has been an MP from here many times before. The Mainpuri Lok Sabha seat has been in the discussion since the first elections held in the country. From 1952 to 1971, the Congress had won from here a total of 5 elections in the country. Although the Congress was defeated by the Janata Party in the 1977 anti-incumbency wave, the Congress withdrew the seat in the by-elections held in 1978 the following year. After that, in 1980, the Congress lost the seat and came back again in 1984 wave. In 1984, the Congress won the last time here, since then this seat has been in the possession of regional parties. In 1989 and 1991, the Janata Party consistently won here. But after forming the party in 1992, Mulayam Singh Yadav fought the 1996 election from here and also won by a big margin. After this, the seat remained with the Samajwadi Party in 1998, 1999. In 2004, Mulayam once again returned to this seat, but later left the seat. In 2004, Dharmendra Yadav won the by-election from here. However, Mulayam returned here in the 2009 elections and kept the seat with him. In the 2014 elections too, Mulayam won from here and gave this seat to his grandson Tej Pratap Singh Yadav. It is important that Jaswantnagar comes in Mainpuri area, which is Shivpal Yadav's assembly constituency. Shivpal Yadav is contesting from the Samajwadi Party this time to form his new party, in which case he can have a big impact on this seat too. Significantly, Shivpal Yadav had a strong hold on the organization even when he was in Samajwadi Party. According to 2014 figures, there are more than 16 lakh voters in Mainpuri Lok Sabha. Looking at the caste equation, this seat is dominated by Yadav voters, about 35 percent voters here are from the Yadav community. While around 2.5 lakh voters are Shakya. This has been the reason that a Chhatra Raj of the Samajwadi Party runs here. There are a total of 5 assemblies in this Lok Sabha constituency. Among them are Mainpuri, Bhogaon, Kishani, Karhal and Jaswantnagar. Please tell that Jaswantnagar is the assembly constituency of Shivpal Yadav. Of these, only Bhogaon went to the Bharatiya Janata Party's account in the 2017 assembly elections, while the remaining 4 seats went to the SP's account. The Modi wave in the 2014 elections had no impact on this seat and Mulayam Singh Yadav, the chief of the Tatkalani Samajwadi Party, won with a big margin. Tej Pratap Singh Yadav also won the election with a huge margin in the by-election held here after he left the seat. Tej Pratap Singh Yadav got around 65 per cent votes here, while the BJP candidate standing in front of him got only 33 per cent votes. In the 2014 by-election, there was around 62 percent turnout. Tej Pratap Singh Yadav is the third generation of Mulayam Singh Yadav's family. He won the 2014 election for the first time in politics, although he got a big advantage of contesting from Mulayam Singh Yadav's seat. Tej Pratap Yadav is also a part of several committees of Parliament. He has spent about 90 percent of his parliamentary quota. He has participated in 16 debates in the 16th Lok Sabha and has asked 226 questions.

translated: * Rahul Gandhi ЁЯСи  again said on PM, ЁЯСК  'Prime Minister Modi himself was doing Rafael тЬИ  over Negotiation' * Congress President Rahul Gandhi once again attacked Prime Minister Narendra Modi regarding the Rafale Deal. This time, citing a newspaper report, he accused the Prime Minister of benefiting Anil Ambani by causing a loss of Rs 30,000 crore to the Air Force. He said that he has been raising this issue for the last one year and now it is also clear from the newspaper report that the Prime Minister had a direct role in this whole matter. The Congress president, citing a report by 'The Hindu', said that the Prime Minister himself was having parallel talks with the French government, while the Ministry of Defense warned that the PMO's own involvement in the negotiations could affect the negotiation of the deal is. He said that the former Prime Minister of France also admitted that under this deal, Anil Ambani's company was selected by Prime Minister Modi himself. He accused Defense Minister Nirmala Sitharaman of telling 'white lies' in the case. The Congress President once again made it clear during the press conference that when he met CM Manohar Parrikar in Goa recently, there was no discussion on Rafael between them and their meeting was just to know Parrikar's condition. message_text: *Modi writes on himself*  My family of 8 lived in a 40x12 feet house тАУ it was small, but enough for us. Our days began early, around 5 AM when my mother would provide traditional forms of curing and healing to newborns and small children. Through the night my brother and I would take turns to keep the тАШchulaтАЩ going for her to use. She didnтАЩt have the fortune of getting an education, but God was kind and she had a special way of curing ailments. Mothers would line up outside our house every morning because she was known for her healing touch.   Then, I would open my fatherтАЩs tea stall at the railway station, clean up and head off to school. As soon as school ended, I would rush back to help him, but what I really looked forward to was meeting people from all over the country. I would serve them tea and listen to their stories тАУ thatтАЩs how I learnt to speak Hindi. I would hear some traders speak about тАШBambaiтАЩ and wonder, тАШWill I ever get to see the city of dreams?тАЩ  I was always curious тАУ I would go to the library and read everything I could get my hands on. I was 8 when I attended my first RSS meeting, and 9 when I was a part of an effort for the betterment of the lives of others тАУ I set up a food stall with my friends to help the victims of the floods in parts of Gujarat. I wanted to do more, but I was aware that we had little means.  Still, even at that age, I strongly believed that God has made us all alike. It didnтАЩt matter what circumstances I was born into, I could be something more. So when you ask me, what my struggles were, IтАЩll tell you that I had none. I came from nothing, I knew no luxury and hadnтАЩt seen a тАШbetterтАЩ life, so in my small world...I was happy.   If the way was ever difficult, I made my own way. I had a great need to look sharp and groomed. So, even though we couldnтАЩt afford an iron, I would heat some coal, use an old тАШlotaтАЩ, wrap a cloth around it and press my clothes тАУ the effect was the same, then why complain?   This was the beginning of everything that I am today and I didnтАЩt even know it at the time. So if you ask the 8 year old Narendra Modi, running around serving chai and cleaning his fatherтАЩs tea stall, whether he even dared to dream about becoming the Prime Minister of India, his answer would be no. Never. It was too far to even think about.  While growing up, I had a lot of curiosity but very little clarity. I would see army men in their uniforms and think that this was the the only way to serve the country. But as my conversations with the saints and sadhus at the railway station grew deeper, I realised that this too was a world worth discovering.   I was undecided, unguided and unclear -- I didnтАЩt know where I wanted to go, what I wanted to do and why I wanted to do it. But all I knew, was that I wanted to do something. So I surrendered myself to God and left for the Himalayas at the age of 17. I bid goodbye to my parents as my mother gave me a sweet dish before I left and put a tilak on my forehead to bless my journey.   I went wherever God wanted to take me -- it was an undecided period of my life but still, gave me so many answers. I sought to understand the world, to understand myself. I travelled far and wide, spent time at the Ramkrishna Mission, met sadhus and saints, stayed with them and began a discovery, inwards. I moved from place to place -- I had no roof above my head, but still never felt more at home.   I would wake up during Brahma Mahurat, between 3 and 3:45 am, and take a bath in the freezing waters of the Himalayas, but still feel the warmth. I learnt that peace, oneness and Dhyan can be found, even in the simple sound of a waterfall. The sadhus I lived with taught me to align myself with the rhythm of the Universe.   So thatтАЩs what I did -- I aligned and experienced revelations that help me till today. I realised that weтАЩre all tied down by our thoughts and limitations. When you surrender and stand in front of the vastness -- you know that youтАЩre a small part of a large universe. When you understand that, any trace of arrogance you have in you melts and then life truly begins.   ThatтАЩs when it all changed. After two years, I returned home with clarity and a guiding force to lead the way.  After coming back from the Himalayas, I knew that I wanted my life to be one that is lived in the service of others. Within a short span of returning, I left for Ahmedabad. It was my first brush with living in a big city тАУ the pace of life was very different. I began my time there by occasionally helping my uncle at his canteen.   Eventually, I became a full time Pracharak of the Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh. There, I got the opportunity to interact with people from different walks of life and do a wide range of work. We all took turns to clean the RSS office, prepare tea and food for colleagues and clean utensils.   Life was rigorous and busy. But amidst all of my duties, I was determined to not let go of my learnings from the Himalayas. To ensure that this new phase of life didnтАЩt take over the sense of peace that I achieved there, I decided to take out some time every year and introspect. It was my way of maintaining a balanced life.  Not many people know this, but I would go away for the 5 days of Diwali. Somewhere in a jungle тАУ a place with only clean water and no people. I would pack enough food to last for those 5 days. There would be no radioтАЩs or newspapers, and during that time, there was no TV or internet anyway. I would reflect тАУ and the strength that this alone time gave me still helps me to handle life and its various experiences. People often asked me, тАШWho are you going to meet?тАЩ And I would say, тАШрдореИрдВ рдореБрдЭрд╕реЗ рдорд┐рд▓рдиреЗ рдЬрд╛ рд░рд╣рд╛ рд╣реВрдВредтАЩ  Which is why, I always urge everyone, especially my young friends, in the midst of your fast paced life and busy schedules, take some time offтАжthink and introspect. It will change your perception тАУ you will understand your inner self better. You will start living in the true sense of the word. It will also make you more confident and undeterred by what others say about you. All of these things will help you in times to come. So I just want each and every one of you to remember that you are special and that you donтАЩt have to look outside for the light...itтАЩs already within you.

message_text: The volunteers is the backbone of every political parties. The aam aadmi party generate from the aggression of the people. Many people across the country joined the party in hope of revolution against the corrupted system. In the 2014 election AAP won 28 seats and made government with the alliance of Congress. After 49 days the government dissolved. some new volunteer join this party during 2014 Lok Sabha election and 2015 vidhan Sabha election. In 2015 party won 67 seats and made the government. During 2015 and 2019 some opportunities volunteers joined with area MLA for their own greediness and benefits. So the MLA conitously are denying and insulting the old volunteers. The old volunteers have enough political knowledge and know the grassroots problems of the Delhi. New volunteer with MLA who don't have any political knowledge and can't defend the party. They only want their own benefit. They don't care about the people and the nation. On the direction of the MLA there is no coordination with the old volunteers supporters and the new volunteer of the party. As a result the last Lok Sabha election and MCD election the AAP lost. If the AAP doesn't call the old volunteers it will loose in Lok Sabha election 2019 and vidhan Sabha election 2020. 2019 Lok Sabha election is good opportunity for AAP to call back the old volunteers in the party. If the old volunteers go to door to door step campaigning they can motivate to the people towards the AAP and can debate with the people and defend the party. Regards  Saroj Volunteer of AAP from malviya Nagar vidhan Sabha.

message_text: --- *From d desk of ABHIJEET RANE* --- *MAN OF THE WEEK:*  *CM DEVENDRA FHADANVIS* --- # This week was *lucky* for  CM Devendra Phadanvis # Who Managed to win over *heart of  ANNA HAJARE*  # Accomplished a long drawn pending *task of tying up with Shivsena*  # and arrive at a mutually beneficial formula of *seat sharing*.  # Anna Hajare's fast was developing in to a *politically inconvenient stir*  # as BJP's allies like Shivsena were trying to *exploit it against BJP*.  # Surprisingly CM Devendra's *friend*  # *Raj Thakare* # who never appreciated Anna's Gandhian philosophy or *self damaging  agitational approach* visited Anna and supported him causing *disturbance to Devendra*  # as he never expected Raj to allian with Anna # who is totally *Contradictory*  to what Raj do & believe. Congress and NCP had *burnt their fingers* with Anna  # so they extended a *meaningless moral support*. # CM Devendra Fhadanvis knew that  # on 7th day *Anna* would be *desperate* to arrive at *compromise*  # so shrewdly CM waited in wings and sent minister Subhash Deshmukh to keep *Anna hopeful* & public satisfied.  # CM Devendra entered the scene of Anna's fast # continuously kept him lingering in dilemma for 6 hours # and finally came out Victorious.  # Prashant Kishor arrived at d invitation of CM Devendra # for bringing Shivsena to *realistic compromise* # and Prashant Kishor did his job so well # that d whole *tension* between BJP and Shivsena just *fizzled out* in a day.  # Now CM Devendra Fhadanvis has only one *task left to complete* # and that is *Ambedkar & Ovaisee form one more alliance* # and don't join Congress and NCP alliance # which is *not impossible* but certainly a difficult one. # Once  Ambedkar and Ovaisee doesn't join AGHADI # then CM Devendra could focus on *RAJU SHETTY*  # and see to it that *he forms one more alliance* with small parties. # Winning Loksabha election depends on Modi's charisma # but even Modi must be relying on CM Devendra # to boost his votes by at least 25% in state.  # I have noticed that whenever CM Devendra is facing challenges # he is at his best. # CM Devendra Fhadanvis's *success* lies in he  being  : *ENTHUSIASTIC, ENERGETIC,  ACTIVE,  ASSERTIVE.* # CM Devendra Fhadanvis has *rearranged the game of the elections* # now let's see how his *plans works out* in both elections. www.livemumbaimitra.com  ---

translated: Abhijeet Rane writes "The Devendra Niti", the key to my success, people often ask me the question how did I achieve this success? How I am successfully leading the Dhadak Kamgar Union, a leading labor organization of the state. And two of my four daily newspapers have reached the threshold of "Mumbai Mitra" Hindi Marathi 17th and "Circle Mitra" Hindi Marathi 11th Anniversary. So today I want to explain the reason. The reason for this is "Devendra Niti". Do not give any political color to "Devendra Niti". Just understand that Indra is considered supreme among the gods. Omniscient honest. Transparent. Fair And full of self confidence. In my eyes, to follow this path is to follow "Devendra Policy" and I will follow "Devendra Policy". I am proud of it. Dutiful. honest. Transparent. Along with being justified, strong confidence is considered to be the way to success. Therefore it is said that if you want to succeed in life, then build confidence in yourself. If we bring thoughts of mistrust and failure into the heart, then we can never succeed. In contrast, people who believe in themselves are always successful. It is a happy coincidence that such is the popular Maharashtra Chief Minister, Mr. Devendra Fadnavis. Maharashtra is making multi-faceted progress under his leadership. The state also has increased social, economic, educational, cultural and industrial self-confidence. All this happened because due to unwavering faith in himself, when Mr. Devendra Fadnavis took charge of the head of the state, the goal before him was to serve the state. Let me tell my point When I laid the foundation of "Dhadak Kamgar Union", a leading labor organization of the state, I had the service of the working community. And when the responsibility of four daily newspapers i.e. "Mumbai Mitra" Hindi Marathi and "Katra Mitra" Hindi Marathi came over me, I had the same feeling in my mind that it is the service of journalism. Due to this service spirit, today Dhadak Workers Union is the leading workers union of the state and Mumbai Mitra is at the threshold of 17th and Katra Mitra 11th anniversary. This is the dedicated service spirit "Devendra Niti". It is believed that we have been born to success and the key to this path of success is service spirit and confidence. One who wants to be perfect, he has to keep his confidence in mind at all times. Service has to be considered paramount. The more confidence, the more service sense, the more success will be achieved.

translated: The salaries of teachers in state-run schools have been increased to Rs 18,500 and pre-primary teachers' salaries by Rs 11,000. Minister of Education C Raveendranath made the announcement via Facebook. The monthly wage of Ayurveda workers has been increased to Rs 6500 and the daily wage of cooks has been increased to Rs 500. Dr Thomas Isaac, Minister of Finance and Planning, made the announcement on wage hike.
